On Fri, Dec 16, 2011 at 4:01 PM, Jonathan Stiles <misterstiles(-at-)gmail.com>wrote:

> Greg,
>
> I believe I paid about $1250 for the Redline/Weber EFI kit in late 2005. I
> think the price is closer to $1500 now.
>
> It only fits a Type 1 Dual Port Motor and would be difficult (but not
> impossible) to adapt to a Type 4. It utilizes a easily  modifiable software
> interface to determine Fuel/Air ratios. However, it is a WOT system (Wide
> Open Throttle) and relies on a narrow band O2 sensor for data, limiting its
> everyday drivability uses. For racing, it has an excellent track record.
> Above 5000 feet, the system gets sketchy. At sea level, it is supposed to
> be very good.
